column3:
Eshana seems on the verge of panicking.

※Please note that the difficulty of this quest has been synced to your current level. Furthermore, you may not proceed with a class or job that is different from when you accepted this quest.
Use the Ananta healing salve on wounded Resistance fighters.
<Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,1)/>, our ssscouts, they've been attacked! Left for dead by sssome territorial predator!
The messenger who limped into camp sssays they were ssset upon along their patrol route in Virdjala.
They're in need of immediate attention, and I have no other sssoldiers to sssend. Quickly, take this healing sssalve and find our injured comrades!
Wait, what is that you're smearing on...oh. Oh! The pain is gone!
Thank you! I think...yes, I can make it back on my own now.

<gasp> Well, that's it then.
I'm done for...
My thanks─you've dragged me back from death's doorstep! I've walked this route a time or two and thought I knew what to expect... I'll be more careful on my way back to the castellum.
I don't know what was in that ointment, but it seems the bleeding's stopped. I'd best report in. My thanks!
Thank you, <Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,1)/>─all the ssscouts are accounted for.
Were you perhapsss curious about the sssalve I had you use? It is an old Ananta remedy that numbs the wound and clotsss the blood...for a time.
As sssuch, these ointmentsss are perfect for emergency treatment out in the field. For long term healing, however, the ressstorative alchemies of your people are far sssuperior.
The Gatekeepers will, of course, ssseek to employ the bessst combination of both. Thank you again for your ssswift assistance.
